product_name: Benefit Cosmetics24-HR Brow Setter Clear Eyebrow Gel with Lamination Effect
summary: SummaryHighlightsClean IngredientsSustainable PackagingBenefit 24-HR Brow Setter Clear Eyebrow Gel with Lamination Effect shapes & tames brows and locks on makeup so your eyebrows don't pull a disappearing act. The custom-molded wand coats hairs from root to tip and the flexible, flake-free formula is easy to apply & quick to dry!
details: DetailsFeaturesCustom dual-sided wand24-hour* staying power100% said it controlled brow hairs***Instrumental test on 21 women**Self-evaluation by 32 women after 1 weekItem 2509015How To UseFor a natural look, groom & define brows with the long bristles to evenly coat each hair.For a feathered look, lift & smooth hairs upwards & outwards using the short bristles.For a brow lamination effect, press hairs against skin to lock them in place using the flat edge.IngredientsAqua (Water), Alcohol, Acrylates Copolymer, Amp-Acrylates Copolymer, Hydroxyethylcellulose, Phenoxyethanol, PEG-12 Dimethicone, Caprylyl Glycol, Panthenol, Butylene Glycol, Gossypium Herbaceum (Cotton) Extract.Product ingredient listings are updated periodically. Before using a Benefit Product, please read the ingredient list on the packaging of your product to be sure that the ingredients are appropriate for your personal use.Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details

reviews.headline: Will buy again
reviews.comments: I bought the mini version to see if I would like it, I love it. It doesn't leave that white cast after applying either. It also doesn't feel like I superglued my eyebrows to my face lol.

reviews.headline: Best Brow Gel Ever!!!
reviews.comments: I literally love this brow gel so much! I use it alone just to sculpt my brows but it works amazingly as a setter over brow pencil too. Definitely would recommend trying it out.

reviews.headline: Great stuff for setting brows!
reviews.comments: I use this with a brow powder.  Once I have my brows how I want them I use this to set them.  It easily lasts 24 hours and looks great the entire time.  I prefer a natural look and can achieve that with this setting gel. It isn't too thick or clumpy--just nice and even.

reviews.headline: Can't live without this product.
reviews.comments: This product has been a part of my everyday makeup routine since I was in middle school. I am now a sophomore in college. This gel has great hold and does not leave crusty flakes like some other brow gels I have tried. I love the way this gel makes my brows look!

reviews.comments: Overall, this is a good product. I loved it forever until recently I started using it and it flakes SOO bad. Anywhere the product gets on my skin gets a white cast that you can peel off like dead skin but its not. Its so bad people point it out to me, my mom thought i had burnt my face and it was peeling skin. This didnt use to happen so maybe its an issue after having it and using it for awhile. It also gets crunchy and very stiff.

faceoff_positive.comments:
I have black, coarse Asian brow hair meaning the thick shaft makes taming them a beating. I've tried all sorts of tricks: soap brows, wax, other brow gels and they would move and / or the product would flake. It made me look like my eyebrows had dandruff! I don't do my brows every day and for years I didn't wear make-up but perhaps a handful of times a year so finding the right product wasn't a priority. In the last couple of years that has changed and I'm so glad I found this product. I used NYX eyebrow wax for years just because I tended to only use drugstore brands. 

This product is worth the price tag. A little goes a long way. It's super glue for your brows!
faceoff_positive.headline: Nothing beats it, tames my coarse brow hair!

faceoff_negative.comments: This was my first time using a brow setter, so it was a completely new experience for me. I enjoyed that it did stay clear and didn't flake. You could barely tell I was wearing it, except for if you look closely, it would look a bit shiny in places where I applied a bit too much. But overall, it wasn't noticeable. It didn't feel crunchy if I applied an even, light coat. However, I applied more towards my inner brows, so it felt a bit crunchy there. I felt it did a better job at lasting longer when I applied it to my bare brows (held up pretty good after 16 hours and withstood a nap) compared to when I applied it over another brow product (Benefit Brow Microfilling Pen). Since I've never used a gel brow setter before, I struggled with how much I should apply the first few times. It also dries very quickly! Near my inner brows, I applied a bit more to control those hairs and realized it dried much quicker than I expected, so it was already hardened before I got the shaped look/setting of my brow hairs that I wanted. I enjoyed the packaging of it and the two different lengths of bristles on the wand! However, I personally didn't notice too much of a difference from before applying it to my brows and after. I don't think my brows are too unruly to begin with, so this product isn't a necessity for me. Nonetheless, it still does hold well enough (especially on bare brows) and extremely well if you apply a lot (though it will feel stiff if you apply too much).
faceoff_negative.headline: Great on bare brows!
